{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "SHELF/vellum_softbody_tetrahedral", "parent": "vellum"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Vellum Tetrahedral Softbody"], "extent": [58, 90]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Tetrahedralizes input geometry, configures it as a Vellum softbody, and adds it to current Vellum simulation."], "extent": [90, 208]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [208, 223], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This tool lets you pick a piece of geometry and configure it as a tetrahedral Vellum softbody.  It will then be added to the active simulation and merged with any other existing Vellum objects."], "extent": [223, 419]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This tool will first simplify, remesh, and tetrahedralize the input geometry before simulation.  Afterward the simulated geometry is brought back into this network and used to deform the original geometry with a ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/pointdeform", "type": "link", "text": ["Point Deform SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/pointdeform"}, ".  A tetrahedral softbody consists of two types of constraints.   Soft ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Distance"]}, " constraints are created along each tetrahedral edge to act as springs to maintain the general shape of the object and ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Tetrahedral Volume"]}, " constraints are created to maintain the volume of each tetrahedron, providing local volume preservation."], "extent": [419, 1001]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/vellum/tetrahedral_softbodies.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [1001, 1052]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": "includeme", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Using Vellum Tetrahedral Softbody"], "extent": [1052, 1104], "body": [{"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Select the geometry object to configure as Vellum tetrahedral softbody."], "extent": [1104, 1184]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Click the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SHELFellum_softbody_tetrahedral", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SHELFellum_softbody_tetrahedral"}, {"type": "ui", "text": ["Vellum Tetrahedral Softbody"]}, " tool on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Vellum"]}, " tab."], "extent": [1184, 1299]}], "container": true}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [1299, 1309], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["There is a ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/clothbodycollider", "type": "link", "text": ["Surface Collider"], "fullpath": "/shelf/clothbodycollider"}, " tool on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Vellum"]}, " shelf that you can use for objects that will be colliding with your softbody. It is essentially the same as the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/deformingobject", "type": "link", "text": ["Deforming Object"], "fullpath": "/shelf/deformingobject"}, " shelf tool on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Collisions"]}, " tab, as they are both designed for deforming objects. However the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/clothbodycollider", "type": "link", "text": ["Surface Collider"], "fullpath": "/shelf/clothbodycollider"}, " does not try to generate a VDB collision object, which is less expensive."], "extent": [1309, 1775]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [1775, 1784], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["You can visualize ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Volume Stress"]}, " by selecting it from the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["False Color Mode"]}, " dropdown menu on the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/vellumsolver", "type": "link", "text": ["Vellum Solver"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/vellumsolver"}, ". This shows you where the constraints have had to work the hardest maintain volume. You can also visualize ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Volume Distance"]}, ", which displays how far they've changed in volume from the rest state."], "extent": [1784, 2140]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/vellum/visualize_stress.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [2140, 2201]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["For specific parameter information, see the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/vellumconstraints", "type": "link", "text": ["Vellum Constraints"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/vellumconstraints"}, " and ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/vellumsolver", "type": "link", "text": ["Vellum Solver"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/vellumsolver"}, " help."], "extent": [2201, 2342]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Working with Tetrahedral Softbody"], "extent": [2342, 2382], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The resolution for the tetrahedral mesh can be changed by adjusting the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Target Edge Length"]}, " on the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/remesh", "type": "link", "text": ["Remesh SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/remesh"}, " and the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Max Tet Scale"]}, " on the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/solidconform", "type": "link", "text": ["Solid Conform SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/solidconform"}, ".  The accuracy of the overall shape can be adjusted with the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Number to Keep"]}, " parameter on the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/polyreduce", "type": "link", "text": ["PolyReduce SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/polyreduce"}, ", although increasing this very high can lead to slow remeshing."], "extent": [2382, 2788]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["By default the Stretch ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Stiffness"]}, " for the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Distance"]}, " constraints is quite low on the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/vellumconstraints", "type": "link", "text": ["Vellum Constraints"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/vellumconstraints"}, " node to make it more squishy. To make it less squishy you can increase this value."], "extent": [2788, 3010]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["To smooth out artifacts in the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/pointdeform", "type": "link", "text": ["Point Deform SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/pointdeform"}, ", you can try increasing the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Minimum Points"]}, " and the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Radius"]}, "."], "extent": [3010, 3149]}, {"type": "include_group", "body": [{"ext": "/dyno/softbody#softbody", "type": "include", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [3149, 3183]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}], "title": ["Vellum Tetrahedral Softbody"], "summary": ["Tetrahedralizes input geometry, configures it as a Vellum softbody, and adds it to current Vellum simulation."]}